Key Match Events: Jamal Musiala scored the opening goal in the 22nd minute
Ilkay Gündogan scored the second goal in the 67th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Germany are the first team to qualify for the knockout stage at Euro 2024
Jürgen Klinsmann believes Germany should still start their strongest team despite having the opportunity to rotate against Switzerland
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match began in a febrile atmosphere with thousands of fans having spent the day partying around Stuttgart
Hungary manager Marco Rossi said on the eve of the match that his side could not afford to make any mistakes
Others: The match was watched by German Chancellor Olaf Scholz and Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban
Germany will play their final group game against Switzerland on Sunday
